reviews.review: Amazing way to end an era.

I thought this was a very epic movie, there were a couple things I wished were either fleshed out more or I wish they did differently. However, overall I enjoyed myself and just because it didn't meet all of my expectations doesn't mean it's a bad movie. The visual effects were amazing, I thought the the combat and action was exhilarating. I don't want to write spoilers just in case but I'll probably buy this as soon as it comes out

Excellent ending to the saga. Don't carry the weight of expectations and let yourself enjoy a movie that is both a tribute to the past films and also a unique story in it's own right. The use of Leia in the film is perfect given the circumstances and it ties everything together the best way it can.

Dang the critics are harsh!  Perfectly fine conclusion to the saga, and even pulled at my heartstrings at the end.  Probably could have used another hour or so to expand on some plot lines, but overall a decent finale.
So much stunning and brave in this movie

Please don't listen to critics!! 

This movie was better than TFA and TLJ. Aside from some rushed plot points and some iffy dialogue, the action was  great and was definitely a fitting ending to the trilogy and the saga as a whole. Is it a 10/10? No, but it is definitely a good, and at times a great, Star Wars film.

Non-spoiler review: Rise of Skywalker is what would happen if JJ did a truckload of cocaine while mainlining Red Bull, asked himself "What if we did Star Wars and Indiana Jones and Harry Potter at the same time!?!"

It's a lot, it's fast, and I'm definitely on board with it. Let's go!
Freaking Christ!  This movie sent me through a GOD DANG rollercoaster of emotions.  Definitely a beautiful ending to an amazing saga!

As a long time fan I believe JJ and Cast did what they could to amend the mistakes of the Last Jedi.  I wish I had more time with the ideas of this movie.  Was it perfect, did it make me happy again as a fan.   Yes!
Overall a pretty good movie, just a few plot points that didn't make a whole lot of sense or where unnecessary. Not my favorite Star Wars, but worth watching for sure.
